# Postdoctoral Researcher

*Dr. Song* is a Ph.D. researcher who completed her doctoral training in the College of Pharmacy at CHA University in 2025.
She received both her Ph.D. and M.S. degrees under the supervision of Prof. Eun-Hee Kim and served as a postdoctoral researcher.

She joined our lab in 2026.
Her research interests lie in translational medicine and translational oncology, with a particular focus on the clinical application of scientific discoveries.
She integrates molecular and cellular experiments with cancer genomics and bioinformatics to develop bench-to-bedside strategies for precision medicine.
